description:
It’s great that Trump won but there will be this lingering feeling of anxiety until he’s inaugurated because it’s unclear if the left will push for radical changes until then.

One of those foolish ideas is putting Kamala on the SCOTUS, as if she’s smart enough for that.

description:
One of the unknown things about the left is whether or not they believe their own crap. However, it’s clear that the establishment relies on the most naive voting base.

Charlamagne has proven he is one of those ignorant voters that the left sees as nothing more than a pawn.

He finds it strange that the left is no longer calling Trump a fascist and a threat to Democracy after he won.

Charlamagne: “Don’t y’all find it strange that now that he’s won, they’re not calling him a threat to democracy? They’re not calling him a fascist ... I would think that, if you really believe that, then somebody’s speech would be about how America effed up and how things are… pic.twitter.com/q0KJplqZUO

title: Charlamagne has stunning realization about Democrat claims Trump is a "threat to democracy"

description:
The reason the left “woke up in a body bag” is because they are so incredibly out of touch with the average American, as they are the party of the rich and the elite. Obviously, this does not win over the vote from the little guy in middle America but these people cannot help themselves, as it’s not possible for them to understand the daily struggles of everyday Americans.

Van Jones claims the reason the left lost is because “conservatives built a different media system.”

Van Jones is 100% right here. They cancelled us, sent us into the digital ghettos. The experienced hardened us, and forced us into building our own platforms. They laughed at our lil ecosystem. But it turned out they were the idiots.

pic.twitter.com/e6c
title: Van Jones admits key reason the left lost the election: “We woke up in a body bag”
